						<div class="postbody">@Tokumaru<br />Out of curiosity, what are the 16 bytes per object used for, in your games? I'm programming an object manager right now and I thought about 11 bytes being more than enough for my case, but maybe I'm missing something I haven't thought of yet. Here's mine:<br /><br />byte 1: object ID<br />byte 2: attributes<br />byte 3: X coord low<br />byte 4: Y coord low<br />byte 5: X coord high (haven't figured out how to do the whole coords thing yet, so I'm reserving these)<br />byte 6: Y coord high<br />byte 7: object state<br />byte 8: current animation frame<br />byte 9: current animation frame timer<br />byte 10: horizontal velocity<br />byte 11: vertical velocity</div>

					
